[1] Australia (New South Wales)
Date: Wed 2 Jan 2019, 3.33 PM EST
Source: The Guardian [edited]
https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2019/jan/03/child-becomes-third-measles-case-in-new-south-wales-in-under-a-week


A child has become the 3rd person diagnosed with the measles in less than a week in New South Wales. NSW Health on [Wed 2 Jan 2019] night said the child had presented to Royal North Shore hospital after becoming infected. A spokeswoman said staff are still confirming details about the latest case with more information expected on [Thu 3 Jan 2019].

It is the 3rd confirmed case in less than a week after NSW Health earlier on [Wed 2 Jan 2019] said a visitor from the ACT was diagnosed with the infection.

The ACT resident was infectious while visiting the central coast and Sydney's northern suburbs between [26 and 30 Dec 2018] [...]

It follows another confirmed case on [29 Dec 2018] when a young adult from Sydney returned from Thailand and was diagnosed with measles.

[... - more]

