******
[2] Portugal
Date: Sun 6 Jan 2019
Source: Outbreak News Today [edited]
http://outbreaknewstoday.com/portugal-reports-three-distinct-measles-outbreaks-82739


The Directorate General of Health (DGS) in Portugal announced recently the 37 measles cases have been confirmed in the country, mostly in adults, since November [2018], according to a Diario de Noticias report (computer translated).

In addition, it was noted that there are 3 different and distinct outbreaks. In Cascais, 24 confirmed cases and 2 probable cases have been reported, which started from an imported case from Ukraine. There is also an outbreak in Oeiras, with 5 confirmed cases, originating in a case imported from the Czech Republic. On the Madeira island, 3 confirmed cases are being investigated.

The DGS also reports that since [8 Nov 2018], 5 isolated cases have been confirmed, "with no known epidemiological link to these outbreaks and that they are being investigated."

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail Rapporteur Kunihiko Iizuka

[The HealthMap/ProMED map of Portugal: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=6248575,42. - Mod.MPP]

