[3] Oregon
Date: Sun 6 Jan 2019, 5:00 AM
Source: The Bulletin [abridged, edited]
https://www.bendbulletin.com/localstate/6821911-151/measles-patient-visited-hood-river-the-dalles


A case of measles has led health authorities to a select group of people in Hood River and The Dalles.

The person with measles visited the OHSU [Oregon Health & Science University] Hospital emergency room in Portland on [Wed 2 Jan 2019]. The virus was confirmed [Thu 3 Jan 2019]. The infected person traveled from out of the county to Hood River [OR] and The Dalles [OR].

Since diagnosis, the person has taken recommended precautions not to continue to spread the highly contagious virus.

Two measles outbreaks over the summer affected at least 4 people.

While there have been no related cases of measles reported yet, the Oregon Health Authority has issued a warning to people who were in the emergency room from 9 a.m. to noon and who visited the places [listed in the URL above] at the end of December.[dates also listed in the URL].

Most people in the area have been vaccinated and have a low risk, the Health Authority said.

Meanwhile, in a separate case, authorities in Clark County are investigating a confirmed case of measles in a child. Clark County Public Health said [Fri 4 Dec 2018] that the child, whose immunization status is unverified, traveled to Clark County from outside of the country in late December [2018].

[Byline: Molly Harbarger]

