[A 2nd report from Fox News stated that the Clark County Public Health Department in Washington reported a confirmed case of measles in a child who traveled to Clark County from outside the country in late December 2018 (see above). The child, whose immunization status is unverified, visited an urgent care clinic in Vancouver, Wash., from noon to 5:30 p.m. on 31 Dec 2018, possibly exposing other patients at the clinic. - Mod.LK]

